,p_plug_source=>wwv_flow_utilities.join(wwv_flow_t_varchar2(
'<h3>APEX Utility #123 is the User Interface to the BOA File Watcher process and contains the following pages: </h3>',
'<p>',
'<b> Manage Process Flow </b>',
' <br>',
'   A Process Flow consists of a series of steps taken on a client file coping it from the source, loading it into the database and disposing of the file. <br>This page provides the means of adding, editing and deleting process flows',
' </br>',
'</p>',
'',
'<p>',
' <b>Manage O/S Programs</b>',
' <br>',
'   Page provides a method of managing the Unix scripts / programs used by File Watch process.',
' </br>',
'</p>',
'',
'<p>',
'  <b>Manage File Patterns</b>',
'  <br> Allows the managing of what files the file watch process will act on</br>  ',
'</p>',
'',
'<p>',
'    <b>Manage Schema Variables </b>',
'    <br> Provides the End user the ability to define variables that will group or identify common processes, steps or folders.</br> ',
'  </p>',
'  <p>',
'    <b>Run Unix Script </b> <br>',
'       Gives the End User the ability to manually execute a set of predefined scripts. </br>',
'  </p>',
'  <p>',
'     <b>View Watch Queue </b> ',
'     <br>',
'      1) Displays a list of active and completed process steps.<br>',
'      2) Allows end user to check on the results of the Unix step.<br>',
'      3) Lists the errors that occur by Unix step.<br> ',
'</p>',
'  <p>',
'     <b>View File Load Queue </b><br>',
'     Provides the latest status of a file process.<br>',
'     Joining File load Queue to File Watch Queue by File Id gives a summary of the file process along with flow details.<br> ',
'     ',
'</p>',
' <p>',
'    <b>Set File Listing</b><br>',
'    File Listings are performed on Oracle directories, setting the file listing displays what is in that Oracle directory.',
'</p>',
'',
'<p>',
'   <b>View File watchers</b><br>',
'   Page displays a list of all DBMS_SCHEDULER FILE_WATCHERS for RDM_LOAD their status, file pattern and the folder assigned to watch. ',
'</p>',
'<p>',
'   <b>View Load Logs</b><br>',
'   Page displays three tables:<br>',
'   1) BOA_PROCESS_LOG: lists all activity performed by all processes.<br>',
'   2) BOA_BILLING_LOAD_QUEUE: Lists the file names scheduled to be loaded.<br>',
'   3) BOFA_FILES_PROCESSED: Lists Files that were loaded with record counts and errors<br>',
'</p>',
'<p>',
'   <b>Restart Process</b><br>',
